%N A392318 Decimal expansion of 37/72.
%C A392318 If three fair six-sided dice are rolled, the probability that the numbers obtained can be the side lengths of a triangle is 37/72.
%C A392318 When three dice are rolled, there are 6^3 = 216 triples (a, b, c) with 1 <= a, b, c < = 6. Among these, exactly 111 triples satisfy the triangle inequalities: a + b > c, b + c > a and a + c > b. Hence the probability is 111/216 = 37/72 > 1/2.
%C A392318 Among the 111 admissible triples, 42 correspond to scalene triangles, 63 triangles with exactly two equal sides and 6 to equilateral triangles.
